</b>111.36<b> Adopt all necessary measures to combat effectively the child labour 
and trafficking of children (Slovenia);  
</b>111.37<b> Undertake efforts to combat illegal trafficking of persons, in particular 
those indicated in the United Nations Convention against Transnational 
Organized Crime and the Protocols Thereto (Libya); </b></p>


<p>GE.13-11815 <b>17 
</b></p>
<p>111.38<b> Implement a national programme to combat trafficking and sexual 
exploitation of women and children (Mexico); 
</b>111.39<b> Take all necessary measures for the protection of the rights of children, 
to prevent the recruitment of child soldiers by parties to the conflict and to 
